<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-14T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-14T19:00:00-05:00" n="133" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/3528: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-14T19:00:00-05:00">October 14, 1931—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>38. Your 71, October 13, 7 P.M.<note n="35" xml:id="d133fn35">Not
                                printed.</note> Dunn is apparently wrong in thinking that first
                            series 1926 bonds have prior lien over second series. Our records
                            indicate and banker’s circular specifically states second series rank
                            equally with first series. Please consult and advise basis of Dunn’s
                            statement.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stemson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>